div><span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-ser=
if;"><br></span></div><div><span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: ari=
al, helvetica, sans-serif;">Natural language is not limited to the written =
modality. It includes and interacts with many others. On the one hand, a me=
ssage can be conveyed through other language modalities, including audio (s=
peech), gestures and facial expressions (sign language or completed speech)=
. It may also be accompanied by social attitudes and non-verbal dimensions,=
 including signs of affect, spontaneity, pathology, co-adaptation with dial=
ogue participants, etc. Natural language processing (NLP) is thus a joint p=
rocessing of multiple information channels. On the other hand, natural lang=
uage is often used to describe concepts and denote entities that are essent=
ially multimodal (description of an image, an event, etc.). Many problems t=
hen require bridges between different modalities.</span></div><div><span st=
yle=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><br></s=
pan></div><div><span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: arial, helvetic=
a, sans-serif;">The objective of this special issue of the journal TAL is t=
o <b>promote NLP in multimodal contexts (several modalities contribute to t=
he resolution of a problem) or inter-modal contexts (passage from one modal=
ity to another)</b>. Thus, the contributions expected for this special issu=
e are, among others (but not exclusively), in the following fields of appli=
cation:</span></div><div><ul style=3D"font-size: 10pt;"><li><span style=3D"=
font-size: 11pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">multimodal dia=
logue, multimodal question-answering ;</span></li><li><span style=3D"font-s=
ize: 11pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">sign language, compl=
eted spoken language ;</span></li><li><span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-=
family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">speech processing, automatic speech =
recognition, speech synthesis in multimodal contexts;</span></li><li><span =
style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">synth=
esis of animated emotional agents;</span></li><li><span style=3D"font-size:=
 11pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">handwriting recognition =
and analysis of handwritten documents;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></li><li><=
span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">=
understanding, translation and summarisation of multimodal documents;</span=
></li><li><span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sa=
ns-serif;">indexing, search and mining of multimedia and/or multimodal docu=
ments;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></li><li><span style=3D"font-size: 11pt; fo=
nt-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">biological signal processing, com=
